4.1.2. PreparedStatement

A PreparedStatement is a special type of query which will allow us to modify
the queries values more dynamically. Instead of giving the executeQuery
something to execute as a parameter we will be giving the object the query
String, replacing those parameters we want to be dynamic with a
placeholder ‘?’.

String sql = "SELECT * FROM table WHERE position = ?";

PreparedStatement statement = connex.prepareStatement(sql);

To replace the ? we use the following sentence replacing Int with the
corresponding data type. The first value is the number of order of the ? in the
prepared statement starting with one. So, if there were multiple ? we first put
its index then its value. To execute the query we use executeQuery(), similar
to regular statements, but with no parameters.

