4.3. Deleting

In SQL we use the DELETE keyword to delete rows from a table in JDBC we use
it in a Statement or PreparedStatement. And just like inserting we use
executeUpdate.

String sql = "DELETE FROM table WHERE id = 1";

Statement statement = connex.createStatement();

statement.executeUpdate(sql);

