4.6. Using procedures

To use procedures we need to call them with a CallableStatement. We
create it by getting a prepareCall from the connection. We use call and then
the function name, we use them similar to a PreparedStatement. If we are
expecting an output value we should register it with registerOutputParameter
then we execute the CallableStatement and we can get the output values.

String sql = "{call procedure_avg(?,?,?)}";

try (CallableStatement cs = connex.prepareCall(sql)) {

cs.setInt(1, 1994);

cs.setInt(2, 2231);

cs.registerOutParameter(3, Types.DECIMAL);

cs.execute();

double avg = cs.getDouble(3);

System.out.println("Average of 2 numbers: " + avg);

} catch (SQLException e) {}

CallableStatement is mainly used for procedures but they can be used to call
functions, but functions usually are queried with SELECT. We just modify the sql
statement and make a few adjustments to the order of our variables.

